author: FROM STAFF REPORTS |
title: H.S. football roundup: Ramsey shuts out Cliffside Park - Sports
text:
CLIFFSIDE PARK â€” Thomas Feehan scored two first-quarter touchdowns to power Ramsey to a 42-0 win over Cliffside Park on Saturday.
The Rams won their third straight to keep them tied with Ridgefield Park atop the Big North American Division standings.
NV/OLD TAPPAN 43, TRITON REGIONAL 6 (at Byfield, Mass.): Quarterback Kevin Martinez completed seven passes for 181 yards and four touchdowns to power the Golden Knights, No. 1 in The Record public school football Top 20, to their fourth straight win. Tight end Jedh Downey caught four passes for 85 yards and two touchdowns as NV/OT opened a 34-0 halftime lead.
EASTSIDE 23, FAIR LAWN 7 (at Fair Lawn): The Ghosts scored 20 unanswered points in the second half to pick up a Big North Liberty Division victory.
Lamar Johnson scored all three Eastside touchdowns in the second half and finished with 206 rushing yards. Henderson Tabora kicked a 30-yard field goal in the first quarter for the Ghosts.
WALLINGTON-ST. MARY MOVES TO TODAY: North Jersey may have dodged Hurricane Joaquin, but not significant rainfall on Friday night into Saturday.
The weather forced the postponement of the Wallington at St. Mary football game to this afternoon at 1 p.m. It originally was scheduled to be played Saturday.
The Gaels (3-0) have beaten Wallington (1-2) in five straight seasons.
